== Sports ==
[[Image:Herzliya's new center.jpg|thumb|Model of new center]]
Herzliya has two [[association football|football]] clubs, [[Maccabi Herzliya F.C.|Maccabi]] and [[Hapoel Herzliya F.C.|Hapoel]]. For many years the two clubs languished together in Israel's lower divisions. Today, Maccabi plays in [[Ligat ha'Al]], the top division of [[Football in Israel|Israeli football]], whilst Hapoel are in [[Liga Alef]], the fourth tier. Both clubs use the [[Herzliya Stadium|Municipal Stadium]].

In addition, Herzliya is one of the two homes for the [[Bnei HaSharon]] [[basketball]] club, which plays its games in Herzliya and [[Ra'anana]] (the club was formed by a merger of the two city's individual teams).

